# Claude Code Environment Documentation
# This file documents the modern CLI tools available in this environment
# Managed via GNU Stow from ~/dotfiles/claude/.clauderc
#
# Note: Claude Code automatically detects and uses these tools when they're in PATH.
# This file serves as documentation for developers and AI assistants.

# Modern CLI Tools Available
# --------------------------

# File Operations:
#   eza (ls)        - Modern ls with icons, git integration, tree views
#   ripgrep (rg)    - Fast grep that respects .gitignore
#   fd              - Fast find alternative (optional: brew install fd)
#   bat             - Cat with syntax highlighting (optional: brew install bat)

# Navigation:
#   zoxide (z/zi)   - Smarter cd with frecency tracking
#   fzf             - Fuzzy finder for interactive searches

# Prompt:
#   oh-my-posh      - Cross-platform prompt theme engine

# Shell:
#   zsh             - With zinit plugin manager
#   zinit           - Fast ZSH plugin manager

# Oh My Zsh Plugins Active:
#   OMZP::git       - 500+ git aliases (gst, gaa, gcam, gp, etc.)
#   OMZP::docker    - 80+ docker aliases (dls, dlo, dcud, etc.)
#   OMZP::sudo      - ESC ESC to add sudo
#   OMZP::command-not-found - Suggests packages to install
#   OMZP::colored-man-pages - Colorizes man pages

# For full alias documentation, see: ~/dotfiles/ALIASES.md
